===Proper noun===
'''Odin'''

# The supreme god of Germanic and Norse mythology.  The leader of the Aesir from Norse mythology.
# The god, after whom [[Wednesday]] is named.

'''Other Names for Odin'''

# ''Óðinn'' (Old Icelandic), ''Wōden'' (Old English), ''Wuotan'' (Old High German), ''*Wōdenaz'' (reconstructed Proto-Germanic form, from [[Wiktionary Appendix:Proto-Indo-European roots|PIE root]] ''*wet-'') ''Odhin'', ''Odhinn'', ''Othinn'', ([[anglicize|anglicizations]], as is ''Odin''), ''Oden'' (familiar form used in mainland Scandinavia).